{
  "stem": "10588.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I had a younger brother, Srulek, and a little sister, Zeisel.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were also born in Ciechanow, Poland.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I-- you know, in our home, maybe because my grandmother was Orthodox, I don't know why-- we didn't celebrate, the same way, birthdays, you know?",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I don't know exactly what their birthday.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I know that, when the war broke out, and I was 13, my little sister, Zeisel-- Zeisele, we used to call her-- she hadn't started school yet.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So she was very young.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My little brother started at three, but he never became bar mitzvah before the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I know that they were younger, but I don't know how much younger.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So instead, for guessing, I rather don't say.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But I know they were the young children.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I was not-- I was the firstborn, but my parents used to tell me that they-- my mother had a miscarriage with the first child, and that they were so thrilled when I was born, finally.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And in fact, knowing this and telling me how welcome, I was welcome-- and something which they didn't tell me, but I took it out myself-- you know, like an assumption-- is that when my mother told me that she used to play the Yiddish theater, but she gave it up when I was born, made me feel that she-- that that was something that was the most important.",
      "word_count": 69
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And actually it was, to her.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The family was the first important.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Assuming-- again, I don't know for sure-- every one-- my mother was one of seven siblings.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My grandmother was one of seven siblings.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And, as I mentioned before, both came from a strictly Orthodox-- both my grandparents and my great-grandparents were strictly Orthodox.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I guess that-- and all her sisters and brothers were Orthodox.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I assume they probably weren't too thrilled with my mother, because she was, she was already playing the Yiddish theater, which was not very much appreciated, at that time, by Hasidic Jews.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I never heard them talking about it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This is what I'm assuming, from knowing later.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But, for me, it was a great advantage, because I was introduced early to Yiddish literature, Yiddish songs, you know, from the point of view.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And also, because my-- they had displayed a lot of affection when we were little, you know.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And Yiddish songs had a great impact on my life, and the Yiddish literature, because they were expressing the values and the times which we lived in.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "For instance, there was a song that I very much remember.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I appreciate it more now than then.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was called the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I don't remember exact all the words, but I remember the meaning of it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it was Reb Lazar, which means Mr.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Lazar, like, [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I'll translate it later.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Which reflected the time, most people didn't have water, so the water carriers was-- that time.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the song-- but he was once influential, well-off-to-do Jew, and then he became poor.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So, to make a living, he carried water.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He comes home, in the first stanza, and the wife-- tired, wet, you know, from carrying-- it's hard to carry the, the pails of water.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the wife complains she doesn't have enough vegetables for the soup.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were poor.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So he said, foolish woman, you have bread and potatoes.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Be grateful for them.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Thank God for that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the third verse, stanza, he says-- he comes home, and the wife tells him, the rabbi sent our son home from school.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I didn't have a zloty-- which means, like, a dollar-- to pay him.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then he responds-- takes out the last zloty-- and he said, to eat-- [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH].",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "To eat, you need.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But to study, you have to.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Be grateful for that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And gives away the last [? penny ?] for everything.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it showed me the importance of studying.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were the people of the book, you know?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Very early, everybody studied and studied.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Like I mentioned, my grandfather studied all his life, with the [INAUDIBLE] rabbi [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, it was like a [INAUDIBLE], where he had, with a lot of Hasidim.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my grandmother, great-grandmother, [?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Itka, ?] after whom I'm named, used to, to-- whatever they-- business they had-- had some kind of business, she used to be in the business for make a living.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, very.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Strictly!",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my grandmother was very-- my grandfather-- I have pictures, I'll show you, of them-- pictures-- beards, everybody, you know?",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Most people, you know, in the, in the small shtetls which we lived were, were religious.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We only had one Orthodox shul in our, in our shtetl, to which we belonged.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
